# .gitleaksignore — Gitleaks false-positive allowlist
#
# These entries are EXAMPLE / TEST credentials that are intentionally
# present in the repository. They are NOT real secrets and do NOT grant
# access to any production system.
#
# Format: one SHA256 fingerprint per line (gitleaks generate-baseline)
# or glob patterns via the [allowlist] section in .gitleaks.toml.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files that contain placeholder / example values:
#   server/.env.example
#   server/.env.production.example
#   examples/.env
#   database/schema.sql        (test_secret_key placeholder)
#   .github/workflows/ci.yml   (CI test credentials)
#
# All production secrets live exclusively in:
#   Railway env vars  (SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_KEY, SECRET_KEY)
#   Vercel env vars   (NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY)
#   OS keychain       (~/.hashed/credentials.json — api_key via keyring)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
